data.chText: 桶
data.enText: a large round container, usually made of wood or metal, with flat ends and, usually, curved sides

data.chText: 啤酒 / 葡萄酒桶
data.enText: a beer/wine barrel

data.chText: 一桶（的量）；桶（石油计量单位，相当于120到159升）
data.enText: the contents of or the amount contained in a barrel ; a unit of measurement in the oil industry equal to between 120 and 159 litres

data.chText: 他们喝了两桶啤酒。
data.enText: They got through two barrels of beer.

data.chText: 石油价格降到了每桶9元。
data.enText: Oil prices fell to $9 a barrel.

data.chText: 枪管
data.enText: the part of a gun like a tube through which the bullets are fired
a barrel of laughs

data.chText: 很有趣；开心；快乐
data.enText: very amusing; a lot of fun

data.chText: 最近生活并不十分令人开心。
data.enText: Life hasn't exactly been a barrel of laughs lately.
(get/have sb) over a barrel

data.chText: （使某人）听从摆布，处于被动地位
data.enText: (to put/have sb) in a situation in which they must accept or do what you want

data.chText: 他们让我们别无选择。我们要么答应他们的条件，要么损失这笔钱。
data.enText: They've got us over a barrel. Either we agree to their terms or we lose the money.
lock, stock and barrel

data.chText: 全部；所有
data.enText: including everything

data.chText: 他把生意全盘卖掉了。
data.enText: He sold the business lock, stock and barrel.
scrape (the bottom of) the barrel

data.chText: （因别无选择）将就，凑合
data.enText: to have to use whatever things or people you can get, because there is not much choice available
be like shooting fish in a barrel

data.chText: 易如反掌；探囊取物；手到擒来
data.enText: used to emphasize how easy it is to do sth

data.chText: 你说干不了是什么意思？这不是小事一桩嘛！
data.enText: What do you mean you can't do it? It'll be like shooting fish in a barrel!

data.chText: （无法控制地）高速行进，飞驰
data.enText: to move very fast in a particular direction, especially in a way that you cannot control

data.chText: 他沿山坡飞驰下来，撞在了一个电话亭上。
data.enText: He came barreling down the hill and smashed into a phone booth.

ex.enText: Two pails of water are needed in order to make a meal.

ex.chText: 你是怎么清理牛奶桶的？
ex.enText: How did you clean the milk pail?

synonyms.bx: 通常用于装液体之物，一般由木头或金属制成。

ex.chText: 我们的葡萄酒是用橡木酒桶放陈的。
ex.enText: Our wine is aged in oak barrels.

ex.chText: 原油价格保持在每桶22美元的低价位。
ex.enText: Oil prices remained as low as $22 per barrel.

synonyms.bx: 指中间鼓起的大桶，多由木头或金属制成，通常用于储存啤酒、葡萄酒等，也常用作原油的计量单位。

ex.chText: 他可以同时提起两桶水。
ex.enText: He can lift two buckets of water at the same time.

ex.chText: 她把碾碎的小麦储存在桶里。
ex.enText: She stored the cracked wheat in a bucket.

synonyms.bx: 可装各种东西，尤指液体之物。

tr: a cylindrical container that holds liquids
a tube through which a bullet travels when a gun is fired
any of various units of capacity
example: a barrel of beer is 31 gallons and a barrel of oil is 42 gallons

tr: the quantity that a barrel (of any size) will hold

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 barreling, barreled

value.def: A barrel is a large, round container for liquids or food.

example.ex: The wine is aged for almost a year in oak barrels.
example.tran: 这葡萄酒已经在橡木桶里存放近一年了。

value.def: In the oil industry, a barrel is a unit of measurement equal to 159 litres.

example.ex: In 1989, Kuwait was exporting 1.5 million barrels of oil a day...
example.tran: 1989年，科威特每天出口150万桶石油。

example.ex: Oil prices were closing at $19.76 a barrel.

value.tran: （石油工业中）一桶的量（相当于159升）

value.def: The barrel of a gun is the tube through which the bullet moves when the gun is fired.

example.ex: He pushed the barrel of the gun into the other man's open mouth.
example.tran: 他把枪管塞进了另一个人的嘴里。

value.def: If a vehicle or person is barreling in a particular direction, they are moving very quickly in that direction.

example.ex: The car was barreling down the street at a crazy speed.
example.tran: 这辆车疯了一般沿街疾驶。

value.def: If you say, for example, that someone moves or buys something lock, stock, and barrel, you are emphasizing that they move or buy every part or item of it.

example.ex: They dug up their New Jersey garden and moved it lock, stock, and barrel back home.
example.tran: 他们把在新泽西的花园刨了个遍，然后将里面的东西一样不落地搬回了家。

value.def: If someone has you over a barrel, they have put you in a difficult situation where you have little choice but to do what they want you to do.
value.tran: 使…受制于人；使…处于不利地位；迫使…做…

value.def: If you say that someone is scraping the barrel, or scraping the bottom of the barrel, you disapprove of the fact that they are using or doing something of extremely poor quality.
value.tran: 凑合用劣质的东西；将就行事

value.def: If an experience is a barrel of laughs, it is very enjoyable. If someone is a barrel of laughs, they are fun to be with.

example.ex: Weddington is the first to admit she's not exactly a barrel of laughs...
example.tran: 韦丁顿第一个承认自己其实并不爱搞笑。

example.ex: The suppers are always a barrel of laughs.

value.tran: 非常有趣的事；笑料不断的开心果
